“Love what you do & you’ll never work a day in your life”

Being a coach is a lot more than getting in front of a group & telling them what to do …
 
It’s believing & inspiring those who didn’t see value in themselves, begin to realize they have what it takes to be better than they were yesterday 

Milestones are achieved when dedication becomes stronger than motivation & if I can be one piece of someone’s journey, I couldn’t be more honored

Coaching for me is not only bringing that early AM energy to wake people up but being that person that pushes them to dig deeper, when all they wanted to do was give up 

People can achieve a lot when they see value in who they are & I am grateful I can be the one that helps them believe they are stronger than they think they are 

Being a coach has & always will be one of my favorite things. Whether it’s coaching gymnasts, young athletes, athletes, or every day people looking to become better

Sometimes I look around & can’t believe I get to do this everyday 

Thanks for letting me be your coach 

-Coach Meg

HERE ⬇️ 

Benefits of Unilateral Movement: 

First of all, unilateral means working one side of the body at a time, with single leg or single arm exercises. Unilateral movement is beneficial to all types of people no matter the athlete level. 

So why should we add unilateral movement into our training? 

it allows your midline to stabilize: What does that even mean? This means you must engage your core and actively think about staying upright and balanced as you work each side at a time. When performing the unilateral exercises, each limb has to work independently in order to maintain that stability and balance. By doing so, this helps with increase in range of motion, engage more muscle fibers, which leads to better core strength. 

Core strentgh/activation: is extremely important in not only your fitness lifestyle but in every aspect of your everyday life. A strong core allows for greater movement and protects the body from injuries/improves posture/performance by allowing the body to generate more power in movement. 

Proprioception improvement: proprioception is the sense of self-movement, the force, body position, and awareness of your body within its surroundings. Having awareness of your body within its surroundings is extremely important when performing dynamic movement. It activates a mind and body connection. 

That was my Thursday tip: enjoy lol

Break down ⬇️ #yesterdaysworkout

Focus lately has been on slow, control, & functional movements 

My knee is going to forever bother me until I actually do something about it - we all know I won’t so anyway ~ 

1. | box jumps with a step down control off, haven’t really don’t box jumps since I dislocated my knee cap, worked my way up to a higher box 

2. | eccentric DB box squats - toes forward, hips tucked under to really focus on core stability 

3. | KB swings - need work & a lock out of the knees at the top 

4. | contralateral loaded elevated split squats to a knee drive to focus on stability in the core and ankle 

Simple movements don’t always mean easy & relearning // learning more about your body not only helps ME but helps me to coach YOU 

👊🏼
